[subsection {Version 0.9.4.18}]
[list_begin itemized]
[item] Tcl 9 compatibility: pdf4tcl runs under both Tcl 8.6 and Tcl 9.0.
[item] [file src/encrypt.tcl]: [method _InitSHABackend] selects the correct
SHA library path under Tcl 9. SHA output uses hex encoding and
[cmd {binary decode hex}] for binary-safe results on all platforms.
[item] [file src/encrypt.tcl]: New methods [method _AesCbc] and
[method _AesEcb] wrap all [cmd {aes::aes}] calls with
[cmd {binary format a*}] to guarantee bytearrays under Tcl 8.6 and Tcl 9.
[item] [file src/helpers.tcl]: [method CleanText] handles non-convertible
characters one by one using [cmd catch] -- Tcl 9 throws instead of
substituting.
[item] [file src/main.tcl]: [method write] sets [option {-encoding iso8859-1}]
in addition to [option {-translation binary}] to prevent EILSEQ errors
under Tcl 9.
[item] [file src/main.tcl]: [method _ValidatePdfDate] checks Unix timestamp
range (below 10^12) -- Tcl 9 accepts arbitrarily large integers in
[cmd {string is integer}].
[item] Makefile: [var {TCLSH ?=}] allows override via environment.
[item] [file tests/util.test]: [option {-translation binary}] replaces
[option {-encoding binary}] (removed in Tcl 9).
[item] [file tests/examples.test]: example PDFs are auto-regenerated when
the Tcl version changes ([file .tclver] fingerprint file).
[item] [file tests/cidfont.test]: test cidfont-9.2 marked as knownbug.
[item] [file tools/tcl9env.sh]: new file -- sets Tcl 9 environment for
[cmd {make test}] and [cmd {make example}].
[list_end]

