[subsection {Version 0.9.4.13}]
[list_begin itemized]
[item] New method [method setBlendMode]: sets the PDF blend mode for
subsequent graphics operations via ExtGState [const /BM]. Supported modes:
[const Normal], [const Multiply], [const Screen], [const Overlay],
[const Darken], [const Lighten], [const ColorDodge], [const ColorBurn],
[const HardLight], [const SoftLight], [const Difference], [const Exclusion],
[const Hue], [const Saturation], [const Color], [const Luminosity].
Requires PDF 1.4 (version is raised automatically). ExtGState objects are
cached per mode + alpha combination.
[item] New method [method getBlendMode]: returns the currently active blend
mode (default [const Normal]).
[item] New method [method linearGradient]: paints a linear (axial) gradient
between two points using PDF ShadingType 2 + FunctionType 2. Options:
[option -extend] [arg {bool bool}] (default [const {1 1}]).
[item] New method [method radialGradient]: paints a radial gradient between
two circles using PDF ShadingType 3 + FunctionType 2. Options:
[option -extend] [arg {bool bool}] (default [const {1 1}]).
[item] New internal helper [method _colorToRGB]: accepts an RGB triple
[arg {{r g b}}], a named color ([const red], [const green], [const blue],
[const white], [const black], [const yellow], [const cyan], [const magenta])
or a CSS hex string [arg #rrggbb].
[item] New options [option -tooltip] and [option -tabindex] in
[method addForm]: [option -tooltip] writes [const /TU] (PDF/UA accessible
tooltip); [option -tabindex] writes [const /TI] (tab order index within
AcroForm, non-negative integer).
[item] [method endPage] now writes [const {/Tabs /R}] into the page
dictionary when annotations are present, enabling correct tab order for
screen readers.
[list_end]

