[subsection {Version 0.9.4.15}]
[list_begin itemized]
[item] OTF/CFF font support in [cmd pdf4tcl::loadBaseTrueTypeFont]:
OpenType fonts with CFF outlines ([file .otf] files, OTTO magic number
[const 0x4F54544F]) are now accepted without error.
Previously these fonts caused [emph "TTF: postscript outlines are not supported"].
[para]
No CFF parser is required: pdf4tcl embeds the font binary as-is and reads
only metadata tables ([const name], [const head], [const OS/2],
[const post], [const hhea], [const maxp], [const cmap], [const hmtx]).
[const loca] and [const glyf] tables (TTF-only) are skipped for CFF fonts.
[para]
PDF embedding uses [const /CIDFontType0] with [const /FontFile3]
([const {/Subtype /OpenType}]) instead of the TTF path
([const /CIDFontType2] / [const /FontFile2] / [const /Length1]).
The ToUnicode CMap and all other font objects are identical.
[para]
A new internal flag [const {BFA($name,isCFF)}] is set to [const 1] for
CFF/OTF fonts and [const 0] for TrueType fonts.
[list_end]

[subsection {Version 0.9.4.14}]
[list_begin itemized]
[item] New method [method addEmbeddedFile]: embeds a file silently into the
PDF Catalog [const /Names] / [const /EmbeddedFiles] NameTree
(ISO 32000 SS7.11.4). No visible page annotation is created.
Options: [option -contents] (raw data), [option -mimetype],
[option -description], [option -afrelationship]
([const Alternative] | [const Data] | [const Source] |
[const Supplement] | [const Unspecified]).
Calling this method when [option -pdfa] is [const 1b] raises an error
(ISO 19005-1 SS6.1.7). Intended use: ZUGFeRD / Factur-X electronic
invoices and other document-level attachments.
[list_end]

